cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.AR 

This paper presents a novel technique for dynamic configuration of deep neural networks to achieve energy-accuracy tradeoffs during runtime. The paper focuses on the design and training of the network, making it likely to belong to the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of energy optimization techniques suggests it could also belong to the category of neural engineering (cs.NE). Finally, the paper's focus on hardware accelerators and embedded systems suggests it could also belong to the category of computer architecture (cs.AR).
